<dl id="n42046d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42046d">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42046d"> 46(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> to live in tomorrow&apos;s / tale</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[quoting from poem cited on xiii]</font> That line &ldquo;to think how his work to-day <mark>would live in to-morrow&apos;s tale</mark>,&rdquo; is a true touch. <small> Stanley Lane-Poole, <a name="SLPS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SLPS"><cite title="source">The Speeches and Table-Talk of the Prophet Mohammad</cite></a> (1882) xvii</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
